      <p class="season-body">Spring is the season the body has been waiting for. After months of contraction and conservation, something in the system wants to move — and the plants that emerge in March and April are precisely the ones to help it do so.</p>
      <p class="season-body">The wild garlic that carpets British woodland floors in April. The nettles pushing up through disturbed ground. The dandelion — derided as a weed, revered in herbal medicine for its relationship with the liver and the lymphatic system. The cleavers that stick to your jacket and, according to the Western herbal tradition, to the lymph as well.</p>
